<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n14026a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14026a">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14026a"> 26(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Let us consider / the fact that we / are this year / about to celebrate / anniversary</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>Let us consider the fact that we are this year about to celebrate the anniversary</mark> of the Reformation, and that we cannot honour our Luther in a better manner than by giving open expression (even if we should, in so doing, encounter personal danger), to those things which we hold to be right and requisite to the welfare of the nation and the Age.&mdash;GOETHE TO ROCHLITZ, 1817. <small> Ernst Boldt, <a name="BFLS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BFLS"><cite title="source">From Luther to Steiner</cite></a>, (1921) 1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
